  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Pilot support to the Grow Africa partnership to enhance responsible investment and inclusive agriculture growth in Africa</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">To increase responsible investment in African agriculture through a regional agri-business engagement platform, making agriculture an engine of African growth. To increase such through transferring an international partnership platform with high mobilisation &amp; convening power to an African home, in support of African agriculture policies, setting-up specific inclusive value-chain partnerships at country level, &amp; promoting internationally recognised standards to ensure investments are responsible, maximising development benefits for the smallholder farmers &amp; overall inclusive agriculture growth.  Will provide an invaluable pilot for DFID&#x2019;s engagement with agribusiness whilst placing a greater emphasis on increasing the potential of farmers to become more commercially profitable, support African&#x2019;s heads of state vision to make of agriculture the engine for growth &amp; ending hunger &amp; halving poverty by 2025 &amp; contribute to a G8 commitment of lifting 50 million people out of poverty by 2022.</narrative>
  </description>
